    <stitle>DT 466 / DT 570 / HT 570 Service Manual - 2004 Emissions with EGR - Fuel System - Installation -
        High-Pressure Oil Manifold Assembly
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc id="S2651203" svcproctype="install" graphiccount="4">
        <title>High-Pressure Oil Manifold Assembly</title>
        <figure id="f2651227" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08053.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil manifold injector oil inlet adapter seal</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Backup ring</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Seal</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat six new injector oil inlet adapter seals with clean engine oil and install onto the
                adapters.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651228" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08052.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil manifold assembly O-ring</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat new oil inlet O-ring with clean engine oil and install onto cylinder head recess.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <specpara>
            <warning>
                <para>To avoid serious personal injury, possible death, or damage to the engine or vehicle, have an
                    assistant help remove or install the high-pressure oil manifold assembly, especially when working
                    within chassis, due to its heavy weight and limited access.
                </para>
            </warning>
        </specpara>
        <figure id="f2651229" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08051.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
            <caption>Installing the high-pressure oil manifold assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Lift assembly up and place onto engine. Align injector oil supply nozzles with oil inlet
                adapters.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f2651230" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figh08/H08090.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"/>
            <caption>High-pressure oil manifold bolt torque sequence (typical)</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install and hand tighten 12 bolts (M8 x 90) to secure the high-pressure oil manifold to the
                cylinder head. Tighten bolts to the
                <hotlnk document="eges2651_249.xml" xrefid="t2651202" appearance="hottext">special torque value</hotlnk>
                and in the circular pattern, beginning from the center.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
